When we talk about the glory of God,

264
00:11:04.300 --> 00:11:06.540
this is who God is.

265
00:11:06.540 --> 00:11:08.700
So it's what like when Stephen preached,

266
00:11:08.700 --> 00:11:10.660
right before he was the first martyr of the church

267
00:11:10.660 --> 00:11:11.800
in Acts chapter seven,

268
00:11:11.800 --> 00:11:15.900
he spoke about God as the God of glory.

269
00:11:15.900 --> 00:11:17.060
This is who God is.

270
00:11:17.060 --> 00:11:18.920
He's glorious.

271
00:11:18.920 --> 00:11:21.140
So there's some implications there to say

272
00:11:21.180 --> 00:11:22.820
that it's intrinsic to who he is.

273
00:11:22.820 --> 00:11:25.380
That means that his glory cannot be improved.

274
00:11:26.260 --> 00:11:28.660
All right, so most of you made some improvements

275
00:11:28.660 --> 00:11:29.820
since you woke up this morning

276
00:11:29.820 --> 00:11:32.060
before you came here and we all appreciate it.

277
00:11:32.060 --> 00:11:35.140
And God doesn't need any improvement.

278
00:11:35.140 --> 00:11:36.860
He doesn't need to touch up anything

279
00:11:36.860 --> 00:11:38.660
when it comes to his beauty and splendor

280
00:11:38.660 --> 00:11:39.940
or anything else for that matter.

281
00:11:39.940 --> 00:11:42.460
He is perfect in all of his attributes

282
00:11:42.460 --> 00:11:45.380
just as he is.

283
00:11:45.380 --> 00:11:48.060
His glory cannot be improved.

284
00:11:48.060 --> 00:11:49.380
That also means in the other direction

285
00:11:49.420 --> 00:11:52.060
it cannot be diminished in any way

286
00:11:52.060 --> 00:11:54.300
and it cannot be removed.

287
00:11:54.300 --> 00:11:56.300
I was reading one of the Puritans this week,

288
00:11:56.300 --> 00:11:58.100
Thomas Watson, he's very pictorial

289
00:11:58.100 --> 00:12:00.020
in how he speaks, uses lots of analogy.

290
00:12:00.020 --> 00:12:01.700
And he talked about how human honor

291
00:12:01.700 --> 00:12:03.940
is not essential to our being.

292
00:12:03.940 --> 00:12:06.480
He talks about how a king can have his crown

293
00:12:06.480 --> 00:12:08.060
and his robes and all of that

294
00:12:08.060 --> 00:12:09.300
and be honored as king,

295
00:12:09.300 --> 00:12:11.780
but that crown can be removed.

296
00:12:11.780 --> 00:12:13.300
The robe can be removed.

297
00:12:13.300 --> 00:12:16.600
He can be brought down from his throne,

298
00:12:16.600 --> 00:12:18.220
but that is not the case with God.

299
00:12:18.260 --> 00:12:20.060
His honor cannot be removed.

300
00:12:20.060 --> 00:12:21.700
It's not like a robe or a crown.

301
00:12:21.700 --> 00:12:24.240
It's essential to who he is.

302
00:12:25.220 --> 00:12:28.580
Another thing is it applies to all of who he is,

303
00:12:28.580 --> 00:12:29.660
all of his attributes.

304
00:12:29.660 --> 00:12:32.060
He's glorious in every way.

305
00:12:32.900 --> 00:12:35.460
I love what John Piper said.

306
00:12:35.460 --> 00:12:36.860
He defined the glory of God in this way.

307
00:12:36.860 --> 00:12:41.860
He says, the glory of God is the outward radiance

308
00:12:41.940 --> 00:12:45.220
of the intrinsic beauty and greatness

309
00:12:45.220 --> 00:12:48.860
of his manifold perfections.

310
00:12:48.860 --> 00:12:50.380
Let's put that a bit more simply.

311
00:12:50.380 --> 00:12:53.660
So God's perfections, God's glory

312
00:12:53.660 --> 00:12:57.100
is shining out of his manifold perfection.

313
00:12:57.100 --> 00:13:00.740
Maybe his glory is shining in lots of different ways

314
00:13:00.740 --> 00:13:03.380
as we come to know God in his various attributes.

315
00:13:03.380 --> 00:13:05.340
So you take like a beautiful diamond.

316
00:13:05.340 --> 00:13:06.180
And you could say like,

317
00:13:06.180 --> 00:13:07.700
oh, that diamond is glorious.

318
00:13:07.700 --> 00:13:09.260
Talking about the diamond as a whole.

319
00:13:09.260 --> 00:13:10.900
But you take that same diamond

320
00:13:10.900 --> 00:13:12.180
and you turn around this way

321
00:13:12.180 --> 00:13:14.060
and you see a different kind of glory.

322
00:13:14.060 --> 00:13:14.900
You turn around this way

323
00:13:14.900 --> 00:13:16.780
and you see a different kind of glory.

324
00:13:16.780 --> 00:13:18.140
And so this is what we see in scripture

325
00:13:18.140 --> 00:13:20.180
when we talk about God's beauty.

326
00:13:20.180 --> 00:13:22.740
It's multifaceted.

327
00:13:22.740 --> 00:13:24.460
And the more you get to know God,

328
00:13:24.460 --> 00:13:27.140
the more of his nature is revealed to you,

329
00:13:27.140 --> 00:13:28.540
then the more you're able to praise God

330
00:13:28.540 --> 00:13:31.420
for his glory in those particular ways.

331
00:13:31.420 --> 00:13:33.180
So we can see the glory of his holiness,

332
00:13:33.180 --> 00:13:35.380
the glory of his power, his kindness,

333
00:13:35.380 --> 00:13:37.660
his wisdom, his love, his providence.

334
00:13:37.660 --> 00:13:39.020
And we can go on and on.

335
00:13:39.020 --> 00:13:42.780
He's glorious in all of his ways.

336
00:13:42.780 --> 00:13:45.300
All right, so it's intrinsic to him.

337
00:13:45.300 --> 00:13:48.500
But also we can talk about God's revealed glory.

338
00:13:48.500 --> 00:13:51.300
So God makes his glory known.

339
00:13:51.300 --> 00:13:52.660
So it's intrinsic to who he is,

340
00:13:52.660 --> 00:13:54.900
but that doesn't mean everybody sees that

341
00:13:54.900 --> 00:13:56.660
or honors him in that way.

342
00:13:56.660 --> 00:13:57.940
But he reveals his glory.

343
00:13:59.620 --> 00:14:01.340
And oftentimes in the Old Testament,

344
00:14:01.340 --> 00:14:02.940
the word for God's glory

345
00:14:02.940 --> 00:14:06.220
is linked with his presence being revealed.

346
00:14:06.220 --> 00:14:08.860
So this is why J.I. Packard spoke about God's glory

347
00:14:08.860 --> 00:14:10.860
or defined it as the excellence

348
00:14:10.860 --> 00:14:15.300
and praiseworthy of God set forth in display.

349
00:14:15.300 --> 00:14:18.860
That's the glory of God is God displaying his excellency

350
00:14:18.860 --> 00:14:20.980
and his praiseworthiness.

351
00:14:20.980 --> 00:14:23.780
It's like the brightness of his majestic beauty

352
00:14:23.780 --> 00:14:27.180
emanating from him like rays from the sun.

353
00:14:27.180 --> 00:14:29.740
You know, I was on my back deck this morning

354
00:14:29.740 --> 00:14:31.580
before sunrise.

355
00:14:31.580 --> 00:14:34.220
And as I sat back there, you see the sun

356
00:14:34.220 --> 00:14:36.460
kind of as it rises gradually.

357
00:14:36.460 --> 00:14:38.220
It didn't kind of come on like a light switch.

358
00:14:38.220 --> 00:14:40.340
It was gradual, it was steady,

359
00:14:40.340 --> 00:14:41.420
and it was beautiful.

360
00:14:41.420 --> 00:14:44.900
See all the different colors as the sun rose.

361
00:14:44.900 --> 00:14:46.460
You see God's glory being revealed

362
00:14:46.460 --> 00:14:47.980
in a similar way in Scripture.

363
00:14:47.980 --> 00:14:51.100
There's a kind of gradual revelation of his glory.

364
00:14:51.100 --> 00:14:53.740
It's progressive as it moves on.

365
00:14:53.740 --> 00:14:57.540
So first of all, you see God's glory revealed in creation.

366
00:14:57.540 --> 00:14:59.420
So in Psalm 19, verse one,

367
00:14:59.420 --> 00:15:04.020
the heavens declare the glory of God.

368
00:15:04.020 --> 00:15:07.640
So looking attentively at the beauty of his creation

369
00:15:07.640 --> 00:15:10.020
tells you something about him.

370
00:15:10.020 --> 00:15:10.940
So if you look at, I don't know,

371
00:15:10.940 --> 00:15:14.340
like one of Vincent Van Gogh's self-portraits,

372
00:15:14.340 --> 00:15:16.300
you look at that and you can see lots of things

373
00:15:16.300 --> 00:15:18.380
about Van Gogh as you look at that.

374
00:15:18.380 --> 00:15:21.500
You can see something about his skill.

375
00:15:21.500 --> 00:15:23.740
You can see something about his likeness.

376
00:15:23.740 --> 00:15:25.980
You can see something about his state of mind

377
00:15:25.980 --> 00:15:27.580
or his emotional state at the time

378
00:15:27.580 --> 00:15:29.100
as you look at these paintings.

379
00:15:29.100 --> 00:15:33.340
So what he's created reveals something about him.

380
00:15:33.340 --> 00:15:35.340
So as we're looking out at creation,

381
00:15:35.340 --> 00:15:38.500
or as I was looking at the sun rising this morning,

382
00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:39.740
it's telling me something about God.

383
00:15:39.740 --> 00:15:42.340
It's speaking of his power, his beauty,

384
00:15:42.340 --> 00:15:45.020
and his majesty, among other things.

385
00:15:46.260 --> 00:15:48.060
But even that is just kind of revealing his glory

386
00:15:48.060 --> 00:15:49.380
in a general sense.

387
00:15:49.380 --> 00:15:50.780
We can't look at that and know,

388
00:15:50.780 --> 00:15:52.460
like this is who this God is.

389
00:15:52.460 --> 00:15:54.140
He's got to tell us who he is.

390
00:15:54.140 --> 00:15:56.180
So his glory is revealed not only in creation,

391
00:15:56.180 --> 00:15:58.540
it's also revealed in his word.

392
00:16:00.060 --> 00:16:01.980
So that's where we have special revelation.

393
00:16:01.980 --> 00:16:04.740
God make himself known specifically.

394
00:16:04.740 --> 00:16:06.380
I'm sure we've all had the experience

395
00:16:06.420 --> 00:16:09.780
of maybe seeing somebody and making assumptions

396
00:16:09.780 --> 00:16:11.500
about what that person is going to be like,

397
00:16:11.500 --> 00:16:12.660
but then you actually get to know them

398
00:16:12.660 --> 00:16:14.380
and find out you were totally wrong.

399
00:16:14.380 --> 00:16:18.540
You totally misread them as you hear from them.

400
00:16:18.540 --> 00:16:21.020
They make themselves known to you.

401
00:16:21.020 --> 00:16:23.660
So we're not left to kind of look at creation

402
00:16:23.660 --> 00:16:25.540
and just imagine what God is like.

403
00:16:25.540 --> 00:16:28.660
He's given us specifics about who he is in his word.

404
00:16:28.660 --> 00:16:31.180
This is where he reveals his glory to us,

405
00:16:31.180 --> 00:16:32.580
his character, his nature.

406
00:16:33.580 --> 00:16:36.740
And so 2 Corinthians chapter three, for example,

407
00:16:36.740 --> 00:16:38.900
speaks about how it is in his word

408
00:16:38.900 --> 00:16:42.100
that we behold his glory by his spirit

409
00:16:42.100 --> 00:16:44.620
as his spirit opens our eyes.

410
00:16:45.460 --> 00:16:47.660
All right, to bring us back to Romans 15.

411
00:16:47.660 --> 00:16:50.180
Here you see that Paul is writing

412
00:16:50.180 --> 00:16:52.780
about specific things about God

413
00:16:52.780 --> 00:16:54.780
and how he has revealed himself

414
00:16:54.780 --> 00:16:56.740
in the Old Testament scriptures.

415
00:16:56.740 --> 00:16:58.060
You see that in that first section.

416
00:16:58.060 --> 00:17:00.360
You see that in the kind of litany of different verses

417
00:17:00.360 --> 00:17:03.400
that he has listed out kind of from verse nine

418
00:17:03.400 --> 00:17:06.720
down to the end of verse 12.

419
00:17:06.720 --> 00:17:08.280
He's showing these verses from the Old Testament

420
00:17:08.280 --> 00:17:10.000
speaking about what God is like,

421
00:17:10.000 --> 00:17:12.600
his mercy and his promises

422
00:17:12.600 --> 00:17:14.000
and about what he was going to do

423
00:17:14.000 --> 00:17:16.820
and how it points us to the coming of Christ.

424
00:17:17.880 --> 00:17:21.320
And so the light shines even brighter now.

425
00:17:21.320 --> 00:17:23.760
Okay, so God's glory is revealed in creation

426
00:17:23.760 --> 00:17:25.160
and in his word,

427
00:17:25.160 --> 00:17:27.600
but the brightest place his glory is revealed

428
00:17:27.600 --> 00:17:30.160
is in the person of his son in Jesus.

429
00:17:30.160 --> 00:17:33.640
The scriptures were pointing to the coming of Christ.

430
00:17:33.640 --> 00:17:35.480
That's where God's glory is revealed.

431
00:17:37.080 --> 00:17:38.520
So John said it this way.

432
00:17:39.360 --> 00:17:40.400
John had been with Jesus.

433
00:17:40.400 --> 00:17:41.800
He said in John 1, 14,

434
00:17:41.800 --> 00:17:43.920
we beheld his glory,

435
00:17:43.920 --> 00:17:45.800
the glory as of the only begotten

436
00:17:45.800 --> 00:17:49.320
of the Father full of grace and truth.

437
00:17:50.180 --> 00:17:51.320
Well, the writer to the Hebrews

438
00:17:51.320 --> 00:17:54.440
in Hebrews one in verse three

439
00:17:54.440 --> 00:17:56.980
speaks about Jesus as the radiance

440
00:17:56.980 --> 00:17:58.280
of the glory of God

441
00:17:58.320 --> 00:18:01.940
and the exact representation of his nature.

442
00:18:02.780 --> 00:18:04.760
Or you can go to a place like Colossians chapter one

443
00:18:04.760 --> 00:18:07.360
in verse 19 where it says in Jesus,

444
00:18:07.360 --> 00:18:10.640
all the fullness of God was pleased to dwell.

445
00:18:10.640 --> 00:18:14.960
In other words, those manifold excellencies,

446
00:18:14.960 --> 00:18:16.560
all of those different attributes,

447
00:18:16.560 --> 00:18:17.680
all of his righteousness,

448
00:18:17.680 --> 00:18:18.600
all of his holiness,

449
00:18:18.600 --> 00:18:19.560
all of his power,

450
00:18:19.560 --> 00:18:23.260
all of that is in the person of Jesus.

451
00:18:23.260 --> 00:18:24.960
So Jesus is truly human,

452
00:18:24.960 --> 00:18:26.320
but he's also truly God

453
00:18:26.320 --> 00:18:28.280
and he did not have to improve

454
00:18:28.280 --> 00:18:30.480
on any of those things.

455
00:18:30.480 --> 00:18:34.240
All of God's glory is revealed in Jesus.

456
00:18:34.240 --> 00:18:36.440
So to see him as to see the very God of glory

457
00:18:36.440 --> 00:18:38.240
manifest in the flesh.

458
00:18:40.040 --> 00:18:42.000
You can see some of these particular glories revealed

459
00:18:42.000 --> 00:18:43.600
in Christ in Romans 15.

460
00:18:45.040 --> 00:18:46.320
So verse eight,

461
00:18:46.320 --> 00:18:48.640
I tell you that Christ became a servant

462
00:18:48.640 --> 00:18:50.680
to the circumcised to show what?

463
00:18:50.680 --> 00:18:53.640
God's truthfulness in order to confirm

464
00:18:53.640 --> 00:18:56.960
the promise is given to the patriarchs.

465
00:18:56.960 --> 00:18:58.200
Okay, so throughout the Old Testament,

466
00:18:58.200 --> 00:19:00.520
God promised that he was going to be praised

467
00:19:00.520 --> 00:19:02.960
by people from every nation.

468
00:19:02.960 --> 00:19:05.720
We have some examples of some of those promises.

469
00:19:05.720 --> 00:19:07.160
So when Christ came,

470
00:19:07.160 --> 00:19:09.160
he showed us that yes,

471
00:19:09.160 --> 00:19:10.360
God is true to his words.

472
00:19:10.360 --> 00:19:11.200
So God is truthful.

473
00:19:11.200 --> 00:19:12.840
The glory of God's truthfulness

474
00:19:12.840 --> 00:19:15.520
is revealed in Jesus.

475
00:19:15.520 --> 00:19:18.480
There's another specific glory spoken of here.

476
00:19:18.480 --> 00:19:19.400
He came why?

477
00:19:19.400 --> 00:19:21.720
Verse nine, not just to reveal God's truthfulness

478
00:19:21.720 --> 00:19:23.360
but in order that the Gentiles

479
00:19:23.400 --> 00:19:26.760
might glorify God for his mercy.

480
00:19:26.760 --> 00:19:30.600
So the mercy of God is revealed to us in Jesus.

481
00:19:30.600 --> 00:19:34.560
We deserve God's judgment because of our sin

482
00:19:34.560 --> 00:19:36.760
but Jesus died in our place

483
00:19:36.760 --> 00:19:40.280
that we instead might know God's mercy.

484
00:19:40.280 --> 00:19:41.880
He received the judgment we deserve

485
00:19:41.880 --> 00:19:44.000
so we know mercy in him.

486
00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:46.520
And there are more things we could say

487
00:19:46.520 --> 00:19:48.120
about Jesus as an attribute here

488
00:19:48.120 --> 00:19:50.080
but we'll maybe leave that for home groups

489
00:19:50.080 --> 00:19:51.600
this week to discuss.

490
00:19:52.400 --> 00:19:54.160
If God is so glorious

491
00:19:54.160 --> 00:19:57.320
that his glory cannot be improved upon,

492
00:19:57.320 --> 00:20:01.440
what does it mean then that we glorify God?

493
00:20:01.440 --> 00:20:02.520
Right? So we're called,

494
00:20:02.520 --> 00:20:04.240
what speaks about God's glory here?

495
00:20:04.240 --> 00:20:07.560
It says we glorify the God and Father

496
00:20:07.560 --> 00:20:08.960
of our Lord Jesus Christ.

497
00:20:08.960 --> 00:20:10.040
We said like,

498
00:20:10.040 --> 00:20:11.320
can't be more glorious than he is.

499
00:20:11.320 --> 00:20:14.440
So how can we glorify him if he's already perfect?

500
00:20:14.440 --> 00:20:15.520
What does that mean?

501
00:20:16.560 --> 00:20:18.480
So it's glorious, not just intrinsic

502
00:20:18.480 --> 00:20:21.560
and revealed ultimately then in Jesus.

503
00:20:22.000 --> 00:20:24.520
We can also talk about the ascribed glory of God.

504
00:20:24.520 --> 00:20:28.960
That's the glory that God receives from us.

505
00:20:28.960 --> 00:20:30.680
So this is when we glorify God

506
00:20:30.680 --> 00:20:31.520
but what does that mean?

507
00:20:31.520 --> 00:20:32.880
How is that possible?

508
00:20:32.880 --> 00:20:35.080
Well, I've heard it compared this way many times.

509
00:20:35.080 --> 00:20:36.000
I think this is helpful.

510
00:20:36.000 --> 00:20:40.400
There's a difference between a microscope and a telescope.

511
00:20:40.400 --> 00:20:42.280
Right? So a microscope is when you,

512
00:20:42.280 --> 00:20:44.360
when you're looking at something that is small

513
00:20:44.360 --> 00:20:46.680
and the microscope's making it appear bigger

514
00:20:46.680 --> 00:20:48.440
than it actually is.

515
00:20:48.440 --> 00:20:49.800
Whereas a telescope isn't doing that,

516
00:20:49.800 --> 00:20:51.400
it's doing the opposite thing.

517
00:20:52.280 --> 00:20:55.520
There's something that's big out there

518
00:20:55.520 --> 00:20:57.760
and it's not making that big thing bigger.

519
00:20:57.760 --> 00:21:01.280
It's making that big thing nearer to view.

520
00:21:01.280 --> 00:21:03.800
All right, so this is what it's like to glorify God.

521
00:21:03.800 --> 00:21:06.240
We're not making him any more glorious

522
00:21:06.240 --> 00:21:08.680
but we are reflecting his glory in the world.

523
00:21:08.680 --> 00:21:12.640
We're bringing his glory nearer to view.

524
00:21:12.640 --> 00:21:13.760
That's why we were made.

525
00:21:13.760 --> 00:21:15.560
We were made in the image of God

526
00:21:15.560 --> 00:21:18.640
to reflect his glory in the world.

527
00:21:18.640 --> 00:21:20.360
When you read about why he chose Israel.

528
00:21:20.400 --> 00:21:22.800
So Isaiah 43 verse 7, for example,

529
00:21:22.800 --> 00:21:25.320
he chose Israel for his glory,

530
00:21:25.320 --> 00:21:27.600
to make his glory known in the world,

531
00:21:27.600 --> 00:21:30.160
to reflect who he is.

532
00:21:30.160 --> 00:21:31.960
Same thing with the church.

533
00:21:31.960 --> 00:21:34.160
We've been given hope in Christ

534
00:21:34.160 --> 00:21:36.600
as we saw in Ephesians 1 verse 12

535
00:21:36.600 --> 00:21:39.400
that we might be to the praise of his glory.

536
00:21:39.400 --> 00:21:41.920
That's what it means to glorify God.

537
00:21:41.920 --> 00:21:45.920
To reflect his glory in our lives individually

538
00:21:45.920 --> 00:21:48.400
and collectively as God's people.

539
00:21:48.440 --> 00:21:50.360
So why does this church exist?

540
00:21:50.360 --> 00:21:52.560
All right, Trinity Fellowship, why do we exist?

541
00:21:53.880 --> 00:21:56.280
Do we exist to meet felt needs?

542
00:21:56.280 --> 00:21:58.000
Like we might have all come in here

543
00:21:58.000 --> 00:21:59.320
for different reasons this morning

544
00:21:59.320 --> 00:22:01.760
or joined the church for different reasons.

545
00:22:01.760 --> 00:22:04.400
We've come for like caring community and making friends

546
00:22:04.400 --> 00:22:06.560
and like I hope that happens.

547
00:22:06.560 --> 00:22:08.960
Maybe you've got a passion to see like new people

548
00:22:08.960 --> 00:22:10.400
reached with the good news of Jesus.

549
00:22:10.400 --> 00:22:11.680
Like I hope that's the case.

550
00:22:11.680 --> 00:22:15.160
Like and you wanna join on the mission to do that.

551
00:22:15.160 --> 00:22:18.080
So those are lots of good reasons to join a church.

552
00:22:18.080 --> 00:22:20.960
We could list out a hundred good reasons.

553
00:22:20.960 --> 00:22:25.720
But the most central reason why we exist

554
00:22:26.760 --> 00:22:29.520
is the glory of God.

555
00:22:29.520 --> 00:22:31.120
The most simple way I know how to put this is,

556
00:22:31.120 --> 00:22:33.320
God is the goal.

557
00:22:33.320 --> 00:22:36.840
And everything else is a byproduct.

558
00:22:36.840 --> 00:22:40.280
Or it's the way in which we glorify God together

559
00:22:40.280 --> 00:22:42.040
as a church.

560
00:22:42.040 --> 00:22:43.840
And we can really mess things up

561
00:22:43.840 --> 00:22:45.880
if we put anything else in the center

562
00:22:45.880 --> 00:22:47.280
that that's what we focus on

563
00:22:47.280 --> 00:22:49.560
and we remove that from the glory of God

564
00:22:49.560 --> 00:22:52.560
being the reason why we are doing that thing.

565
00:22:52.560 --> 00:22:54.920
So the glory of God is at the center of all that we do.

566
00:22:54.920 --> 00:22:56.800
And by the way, that raises the quality

567
00:22:56.800 --> 00:22:59.000
of everything that we do as well.

568
00:22:59.000 --> 00:23:03.000
Like if we want to be part of like a caring community,

569
00:23:03.000 --> 00:23:05.600
well, the best way we can become a caring community

570
00:23:05.600 --> 00:23:09.920
is by caring for one another in a way that glorifies God.

571
00:23:09.920 --> 00:23:11.600
If we wanna reach new people like,

572
00:23:11.600 --> 00:23:12.920
well, the best way to do that

573
00:23:12.920 --> 00:23:15.280
is to understand who God is

574
00:23:15.280 --> 00:23:16.720
and his heart for the community

575
00:23:16.720 --> 00:23:18.160
and to glorify God in the way

576
00:23:18.160 --> 00:23:21.060
that we're making Christ known in the community.

577
00:23:22.280 --> 00:23:23.720
You know, you might think of like,

578
00:23:23.720 --> 00:23:26.080
I don't know if you say like, could you cook a meal?

579
00:23:26.080 --> 00:23:28.200
I'm like, well, cook a meal for who?

580
00:23:28.200 --> 00:23:30.360
Like is this like my kid on a Saturday?

581
00:23:30.360 --> 00:23:32.520
Like it might be, I was about to say peanut butter

582
00:23:32.520 --> 00:23:34.120
and jelly, but none of them would have eaten that.

583
00:23:34.120 --> 00:23:35.640
None of them like peanut butter.

584
00:23:35.640 --> 00:23:36.760
So I might make them a sandwich.

585
00:23:36.760 --> 00:23:38.360
But if you say, well, I need you to cook a meal

586
00:23:38.360 --> 00:23:41.400
but it's gonna be for like this award-winning chef.

587
00:23:41.400 --> 00:23:42.920
Like I'm gonna cook them a different meal.

588
00:23:42.920 --> 00:23:46.120
Like so who it's for affects the quality

589
00:23:46.120 --> 00:23:47.920
of what's actually happening.

590
00:23:47.920 --> 00:23:48.760
Okay.

591
00:23:51.200 --> 00:23:52.560
So what is it?

592
00:23:52.560 --> 00:23:55.840
What's the quality of our worship like here?

593
00:23:58.160 --> 00:23:59.280
That's a good question for us to ask.

594
00:23:59.280 --> 00:24:01.200
So let's look then at the worship of God.

595
00:24:01.200 --> 00:24:02.960
We kinda see what the glory of God is.

596
00:24:02.960 --> 00:24:05.000
What does it mean to glorify God in a way

597
00:24:05.000 --> 00:24:07.640
that is honoring to him?

598
00:24:08.960 --> 00:24:13.080
So our opening scripture Psalm 29 verse two

599
00:24:13.080 --> 00:24:15.760
ties glory and worship together.

600
00:24:16.680 --> 00:24:19.880
So verse two, it's on the front of your worship guide.

601
00:24:20.800 --> 00:24:25.440
Ascribe to the Lord the glory due his name.

602
00:24:25.440 --> 00:24:27.360
And then it says, kinda repeats the same idea

603
00:24:27.360 --> 00:24:30.680
but in a different way, worship the Lord

604
00:24:30.680 --> 00:24:34.340
in the beauty or splendor of holiness.

605
00:24:35.240 --> 00:24:38.200
So and this is the kind of God exalting worship

606
00:24:38.200 --> 00:24:40.960
Paul is hoping to provoke in the life of the church

607
00:24:40.960 --> 00:24:42.480
as he writes here.

608
00:24:42.480 --> 00:24:44.640
He's longing that together with one voice

609
00:24:44.640 --> 00:24:46.680
they might glorify the God and father

610
00:24:46.680 --> 00:24:48.160
of our Lord Jesus Christ.

611
00:24:48.160 --> 00:24:50.680
That is worship.

612
00:24:50.680 --> 00:24:52.200
But the word worship isn't used here

613
00:24:52.200 --> 00:24:53.760
but that's what's going on here.

614
00:24:53.760 --> 00:24:57.800
Glorifying God through our worship.

615
00:24:57.800 --> 00:25:00.600
Specifically through the quality of our worship.

616
00:25:02.440 --> 00:25:05.960
A few days ago, I was sitting in a coffee shop

617
00:25:05.960 --> 00:25:09.440
on a big shock and I was having a chat with a guy

618
00:25:09.440 --> 00:25:11.520
who's never been to Trinity before

619
00:25:11.520 --> 00:25:13.320
and he asked me, he said,

620
00:25:13.320 --> 00:25:16.480
oh, what's your worship like at Trinity?

621
00:25:16.480 --> 00:25:17.980
That's an interesting question.

622
00:25:19.880 --> 00:25:22.080
What did he actually mean by that?

623
00:25:22.080 --> 00:25:23.880
What's your worship like at Trinity?

624
00:25:24.840 --> 00:25:27.840
Well, I answered what he was actually asking

625
00:25:27.840 --> 00:25:29.120
and you know what he was asking.

626
00:25:29.120 --> 00:25:31.400
He was asking, well, what's the music like at Trinity?

627
00:25:31.400 --> 00:25:34.780
Like we've somehow turned that into like,

628
00:25:34.780 --> 00:25:38.240
we just mean like the evangelical world in the West

629
00:25:38.440 --> 00:25:40.880
made worship synonymous with singing.

630
00:25:42.560 --> 00:25:44.680
By the way, that's a very recent development.

631
00:25:44.680 --> 00:25:47.720
It's only within like the past like 50 years or so

632
00:25:47.720 --> 00:25:49.920
where in our particular part of the world

633
00:25:49.920 --> 00:25:52.240
where we've started equating the word worship

634
00:25:52.240 --> 00:25:55.760
and singing as being synonymous as the same thing.

635
00:25:55.760 --> 00:25:57.640
Now, don't get me wrong.

636
00:25:57.640 --> 00:26:00.920
Our worship includes our singing.

637
00:26:00.920 --> 00:26:02.280
So you look at verse nine.

638
00:26:02.280 --> 00:26:03.960
You know, this worship recall to,

639
00:26:03.960 --> 00:26:06.400
it involves us singing to the Lord.

640
00:26:08.640 --> 00:26:10.440
But the quality of our worship,

641
00:26:10.440 --> 00:26:11.520
but it's about more than that.

642
00:26:11.520 --> 00:26:13.080
But and also the quality of our worship

643
00:26:13.080 --> 00:26:16.080
isn't about the quality of our singing.

644
00:26:16.080 --> 00:26:18.040
Though I appreciate all of the musicians and singers

645
00:26:18.040 --> 00:26:19.840
and all the rest of you guys are great.

646
00:26:19.840 --> 00:26:21.200
But that's not what's being addressed here.

647
00:26:21.200 --> 00:26:22.200
He's not saying I want you guys

648
00:26:22.200 --> 00:26:23.960
to just sing a little bit better.

649
00:26:23.960 --> 00:26:25.280
When he says I want you to with one voice

650
00:26:25.280 --> 00:26:26.560
to glorify God in harmony.

651
00:26:26.560 --> 00:26:28.840
Like your harmonies are a bit off.

652
00:26:28.840 --> 00:26:30.240
What's he talking about?

653
00:26:32.080 --> 00:26:35.720
What does it mean to worship God in a quality way?

654
00:26:36.560 --> 00:26:38.840
Well, we need to understand what worship is.

655
00:26:38.840 --> 00:26:41.680
Edmund Clowney, once again, to go back to him,

656
00:26:41.680 --> 00:26:46.240
he said this, worship is the response of the creature

657
00:26:46.240 --> 00:26:49.140
to the revealed glory of the creator.

658
00:26:50.720 --> 00:26:52.560
All right, so we see this glory

659
00:26:52.560 --> 00:26:55.760
that God has revealed to us in his word and in Christ.

660
00:26:55.760 --> 00:26:58.760
And true worship is when we respond rightly

661
00:26:58.760 --> 00:27:00.880
to what he has shown us about himself.

662
00:27:02.240 --> 00:27:05.560
And that finds its expression in lots of different ways.

663
00:27:05.560 --> 00:27:07.000
Let's just break it down simply.

664
00:27:07.000 --> 00:27:10.880
It involves our heads, our hearts and our hands.

665
00:27:10.880 --> 00:27:12.600
And all of that is worship.

666
00:27:12.600 --> 00:27:16.760
So worship involves our heads as we respond to the Lord.

667
00:27:16.760 --> 00:27:19.240
If worship is our response to the revelation

668
00:27:19.240 --> 00:27:22.520
of God's glory, then that means we need to be listening

669
00:27:22.520 --> 00:27:24.400
and hearing and heeding to the truth

670
00:27:24.400 --> 00:27:26.440
of what God has told us about himself.

671
00:27:26.440 --> 00:27:29.640
We've got to actually think about who God is.

672
00:27:29.640 --> 00:27:30.840
It's not just a feeling.

673
00:27:32.160 --> 00:27:33.800
And it's not just an action.

674
00:27:33.840 --> 00:27:36.000
Thinking about the actual God

675
00:27:36.000 --> 00:27:37.240
who's revealed himself in his word.

676
00:27:37.240 --> 00:27:41.720
So what did Jesus say in John 4 verses 23 and 24,

677
00:27:41.720 --> 00:27:44.160
that God is seeking those who will worship him

678
00:27:44.160 --> 00:27:47.760
in what, spirit and truth.

679
00:27:47.760 --> 00:27:51.240
So true worship involves the truth.

680
00:27:51.240 --> 00:27:52.960
If we're gonna worship God rightly,

681
00:27:52.960 --> 00:27:56.240
then that means thinking about him rightly as well.

682
00:27:56.240 --> 00:27:59.920
We're not just feeling good about our general ideas

683
00:27:59.920 --> 00:28:02.240
about a vague God.

684
00:28:02.240 --> 00:28:03.920
If that's what worship is,

685
00:28:03.920 --> 00:28:07.080
we just need to really pump up the feelings.

686
00:28:07.080 --> 00:28:10.720
Well, I mean, there's better ways that we could do that.

687
00:28:10.720 --> 00:28:14.560
We just really get our emotions pumping here.

688
00:28:14.560 --> 00:28:18.200
We've got to be thinking rightly about God as well.

689
00:28:21.320 --> 00:28:23.240
And this is true individually, but also as a church.

690
00:28:23.240 --> 00:28:26.520
It's important that the word is central in our worship.

691
00:28:26.520 --> 00:28:27.360
Well, let's move on.

692
00:28:27.360 --> 00:28:28.520
It doesn't just involve our heads,

693
00:28:28.520 --> 00:28:30.800
it also involves our hearts.

694
00:28:30.800 --> 00:28:33.360
So worship that glorifies God is worship

695
00:28:33.360 --> 00:28:35.280
that comes from the heart,

696
00:28:35.280 --> 00:28:38.200
from a heart that is truly after him.

697
00:28:38.200 --> 00:28:40.440
When verse five in Romans 15 speaks

698
00:28:40.440 --> 00:28:42.600
about living together in harmony,

699
00:28:42.600 --> 00:28:45.200
the word living together actually conveys a sense

700
00:28:45.200 --> 00:28:48.400
of having a similar,

701
00:28:48.400 --> 00:28:51.160
or a oneness of inner purpose

702
00:28:51.160 --> 00:28:54.480
or a shared passion, living together in harmony.

703
00:28:54.480 --> 00:28:57.880
Share the same passion, be of the same heart and mind.

704
00:28:58.920 --> 00:29:00.520
We'll look at this more in detail next week,

705
00:29:00.520 --> 00:29:04.720
but they were having these kind of worship wars

