00:30:56.640 --> 00:30:58.400
It's recognizing the honor of somebody

749
00:30:58.400 --> 00:31:01.760
by bowing yourself down to the ground.

750
00:31:01.760 --> 00:31:03.760
And this is how we honor the Lord in worship

751
00:31:03.760 --> 00:31:07.440
by bowing before Him.

752
00:31:07.440 --> 00:31:10.360
So the quality of our hearts in worship

753
00:31:10.360 --> 00:31:12.880
isn't like our impressiveness or all the good things

754
00:31:12.880 --> 00:31:15.360
that we can bring before the Lord.

755
00:31:15.360 --> 00:31:16.520
The quality of...

756
00:31:22.560 --> 00:31:25.640
The quality of our worship will be seen in coming before God.

757
00:31:25.640 --> 00:31:30.000
Let's put it this way, in humility before the Lord.

758
00:31:30.000 --> 00:31:33.280
Not trying to bring our own impressiveness before Him

759
00:31:33.280 --> 00:31:36.880
but holding out the empty hands of faith in our need,

760
00:31:36.880 --> 00:31:39.280
receiving His grace and glorifying God

761
00:31:39.280 --> 00:31:41.280
because of what He has done.

762
00:31:41.280 --> 00:31:44.160
Saying, none of this comes from me, it's all from you

763
00:31:44.160 --> 00:31:46.880
and you are the one who deserves all the glory.

764
00:31:46.880 --> 00:31:50.520
That is what it is to bow before the Lord in worship.

765
00:31:53.280 --> 00:31:56.280
It's like what Paul says in Romans 12, 1.

766
00:31:56.280 --> 00:31:59.280
Having just explained all the glories of the gospel

767
00:31:59.280 --> 00:32:01.280
in chapters 1 to 11, he says,

768
00:32:01.280 --> 00:32:04.280
I appeal to you, therefore, brothers, by the mercies of God

769
00:32:04.280 --> 00:32:08.280
that you present your bodies as a living sacrifice to the Lord.

770
00:32:10.280 --> 00:32:15.280
Which is your spiritual worship.

771
00:32:15.280 --> 00:32:18.280
So we're seeing this is our Lord.

772
00:32:18.280 --> 00:32:20.280
He is worthy to be praised.

773
00:32:20.280 --> 00:32:22.280
And He's done this for us in Christ.

774
00:32:22.280 --> 00:32:24.280
And so we're giving ourselves to Him.

775
00:32:24.280 --> 00:32:26.280
That's the service He's looking for.

776
00:32:26.280 --> 00:32:28.280
By the way, that's the other Old Testament word

777
00:32:28.280 --> 00:32:30.280
used for worship is service.

778
00:32:30.280 --> 00:32:33.280
So we're offering ourselves up to Him in service.

779
00:32:33.280 --> 00:32:36.280
If you want to know what the English word stands for

780
00:32:36.280 --> 00:32:39.280
is worship is where we get that word.

781
00:32:39.280 --> 00:32:41.280
It's a great word for what worship truly is.

782
00:32:41.280 --> 00:32:44.280
It's recognizing the worth of Jesus

783
00:32:44.280 --> 00:32:47.280
and giving ourselves freely to Him.

784
00:32:47.280 --> 00:32:49.280
Lastly, it involves not just our head

785
00:32:49.280 --> 00:32:52.280
and our hearts, but also our hands.

786
00:32:54.280 --> 00:32:57.280
So when God makes Himself known to us in our minds

787
00:32:57.280 --> 00:32:59.280
and we give Him our hearts,

788
00:32:59.280 --> 00:33:03.280
that then finds an outward expression in our actions.

789
00:33:03.280 --> 00:33:06.280
Now here in Romans 15, that is what's being addressed

790
00:33:06.280 --> 00:33:08.280
as how we fellowship with one another,

791
00:33:08.280 --> 00:33:09.280
how we treat one another.

792
00:33:09.280 --> 00:33:11.280
And that is an act of worship

793
00:33:11.280 --> 00:33:14.280
as we care for one another as we've been cared for by Christ.

794
00:33:14.280 --> 00:33:17.280
It involves more than that too.

795
00:33:17.280 --> 00:33:19.280
It's other areas of service.

796
00:33:19.280 --> 00:33:22.280
So Hebrews 13 verses 15 and 16 says,

797
00:33:22.280 --> 00:33:24.280
through Christ,

798
00:33:24.280 --> 00:33:27.280
then let us continually offer up a sacrifice

799
00:33:27.280 --> 00:33:29.280
of praise to God.

800
00:33:29.280 --> 00:33:33.280
That is the fruit of lips that acknowledge His name.

801
00:33:33.280 --> 00:33:37.280
Alright, so as we praise God, that is worship.

802
00:33:37.280 --> 00:33:40.280
But also it says, do not neglect to do good

803
00:33:40.280 --> 00:33:42.280
and to share what you have

804
00:33:42.280 --> 00:33:45.280
for such sacrifices are pleasing to God

805
00:33:45.280 --> 00:33:47.280
as we care for the needs of others.

806
00:33:47.280 --> 00:33:51.280
That is an act of worship to God.

807
00:33:51.280 --> 00:33:53.280
So the united worship that we are called to

808
00:33:53.280 --> 00:33:57.280
involves lots of practical things.

809
00:33:57.280 --> 00:33:59.280
And it involves things like we're doing today,

810
00:33:59.280 --> 00:34:01.280
prayer, listening to God's word.

811
00:34:01.280 --> 00:34:03.280
It involves things like receiving communion,

812
00:34:03.280 --> 00:34:05.280
caring for one another in community, singing praises,

813
00:34:05.280 --> 00:34:07.280
and proclaiming Christ to the world.

814
00:34:07.280 --> 00:34:11.280
All of that is worship.

815
00:34:11.280 --> 00:34:13.280
And I've said it before, I'm going to say it again.

816
00:34:13.280 --> 00:34:16.280
I appreciate all the ways that people serve in this church.

817
00:34:16.280 --> 00:34:19.280
And it's been wonderful to see.

818
00:34:19.280 --> 00:34:23.280
And all of that is worship if it's done

819
00:34:23.280 --> 00:34:26.280
with a heart that is after the Lord.

820
00:34:26.280 --> 00:34:28.280
So I hope we continue to serve

821
00:34:28.280 --> 00:34:31.280
within the life of this church.

822
00:34:31.280 --> 00:34:34.280
But don't serve because you think

823
00:34:34.280 --> 00:34:37.280
the church plant is worth it.

824
00:34:37.280 --> 00:34:40.280
Because pretty soon it's not going to feel worth it anymore

825
00:34:40.280 --> 00:34:42.280
when it gets hard.

826
00:34:42.280 --> 00:34:45.280
And don't serve out of a kind of self fulfillment.

827
00:34:45.280 --> 00:34:47.280
Like this is my area.

828
00:34:47.280 --> 00:34:49.280
This is tied to my identity.

829
00:34:49.280 --> 00:34:51.280
Like this is where I'm serving.

830
00:34:51.280 --> 00:34:53.280
What should motivate us in our service,

831
00:34:53.280 --> 00:34:55.280
whether it's children's ministry or music

832
00:34:55.280 --> 00:34:57.280
or a day like Founders Day, yesterday,

833
00:34:57.280 --> 00:34:59.280
or whatever area of service you're serving in,

834
00:34:59.280 --> 00:35:01.280
setting up, what should motivate us

835
00:35:01.280 --> 00:35:03.280
is the worthiness of Jesus.

836
00:35:03.280 --> 00:35:05.280
He is why we do it.

837
00:35:05.280 --> 00:35:07.280
It flows from a passion to glorify God.

838
00:35:07.280 --> 00:35:09.280
And if we all have that same passion,

839
00:35:09.280 --> 00:35:11.280
that is what's going to unite us together.

840
00:35:11.280 --> 00:35:13.280
And we're going to glorify in our worship.

841
00:35:13.280 --> 00:35:15.280
Let me end with this.

842
00:35:15.280 --> 00:35:17.280
I saw a remarkable photo.

843
00:35:17.280 --> 00:35:19.280
It's taken back in 2015.

844
00:35:19.280 --> 00:35:21.280
And it's of a humpback whale.

845
00:35:21.280 --> 00:35:23.280
Beautiful, elusive.

846
00:35:23.280 --> 00:35:25.280
This person took the photo.

847
00:35:25.280 --> 00:35:27.280
But what is so remarkable about this photo

848
00:35:27.280 --> 00:35:29.280
of this humpback whale kind of coming out of the water,

849
00:35:29.280 --> 00:35:31.280
revealing his majesty, so to speak,

850
00:35:31.280 --> 00:35:34.280
is the guy in the picture behind it.

851
00:35:34.280 --> 00:35:36.280
Because there's a guy in a boat

852
00:35:36.280 --> 00:35:38.280
behind the humpback whale.

853
00:35:38.280 --> 00:35:41.280
And he's completely oblivious to what's in front of him.

854
00:35:41.280 --> 00:35:43.280
He's glued to his phone.

855
00:35:43.280 --> 00:35:46.280
He's just scrolling through his phone.

856
00:35:46.280 --> 00:35:48.280
Is it because he's just scrolling?

857
00:35:48.280 --> 00:35:50.280
He misses the majesty,

858
00:35:50.280 --> 00:35:52.280
the greater glory that is right

859
00:35:52.280 --> 00:35:56.280
in front of him by just scrolling away.

860
00:35:56.280 --> 00:35:59.280
So as we're coming to the Lord in prayer,

861
00:35:59.280 --> 00:36:01.280
let's ask ourselves this.

862
00:36:04.280 --> 00:36:06.280
Am I captivated by the worthiness

863
00:36:06.280 --> 00:36:11.280
of Jesus, or am I distracted by lesser things?

864
00:36:11.280 --> 00:36:13.280
Is he the one I treasure above all else?

865
00:36:13.280 --> 00:36:16.280
Is he at the center of my thoughts, my motivations,

866
00:36:16.280 --> 00:36:19.280
the reason why I exist, the reason why I serve?

867
00:36:22.280 --> 00:36:25.280
Well, let's all offer ourselves up afresh to him

868
00:36:25.280 --> 00:36:27.280
in worship because he is worthy. Let's pray.

869
00:36:30.280 --> 00:36:33.280
Lord, I pray that you would make us a people

870
00:36:33.280 --> 00:36:35.280
who glorify you

871
00:36:35.280 --> 00:36:38.280
by uniting together in praise of your name.

872
00:36:38.280 --> 00:36:41.280
We're afraid that you'd make us a people of worship.

873
00:36:41.280 --> 00:36:44.280
Lord, it is only by your spirit that we are able to see

874
00:36:44.280 --> 00:36:47.280
more and more of your worthiness,

875
00:36:47.280 --> 00:36:50.280
the glories you've revealed to us in Jesus.

876
00:36:50.280 --> 00:36:54.280
Lord, I pray that you'd help us to see more and more of your beauty.

877
00:36:55.280 --> 00:36:58.280
And so I pray that as you open our eyes to see more of you,

878
00:36:58.280 --> 00:37:01.280
that we would be ready and willing and eager

879
00:37:01.280 --> 00:37:03.280
to give ourselves completely to you

880
00:37:03.280 --> 00:37:05.280
because you are worth it.

881
00:37:07.280 --> 00:37:09.280
And so all too often,

882
00:37:09.280 --> 00:37:11.280
would I and I know the rest of us

883
00:37:11.280 --> 00:37:14.280
get distracted by the things of this world

884
00:37:14.280 --> 00:37:18.280
and I pray that you would draw our minds and our hearts

885
00:37:18.280 --> 00:37:20.280
and our wills back to you.

886
00:37:20.280 --> 00:37:22.280
I pray that you'd make us a people

887
00:37:22.280 --> 00:37:25.280
who truly worship you from our hearts

888
00:37:25.280 --> 00:37:27.280
and with our lives together for the glory of your name.

889
00:37:27.280 --> 00:37:29.280
Amen.

